		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />just checking in to say that everything is working great for me on this firmware!<br /><br />simple process: first i took out the two screws in the back of the powerpak just to check what version i had and it looked the same as <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=106411#p106411" class="postlink">effowe's here</a>, rev H. followed the instructions <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=107414#p107414" class="postlink">in this post</a> and when i turned it on and got a bit of a scare as it just sat at the powerpak screen. turned it off and back on again and it loaded into the updater fine, so i'm not sure why it needed 2 tries.<br /><br />but yeah now there's this really good looking menu on my powerpak and all the long filenames display better (couldn't distinguish <span style="color: #00BF40">Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles - Tournament Fighters</span> from <span style="color: #00BF40">Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles IV - Turtles in Time</span> when they used to get truncated). thanks a lot Ramsis  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_mrgreen.gif" alt=":mrgreen:" title="Mr. Green" /> definite upgrade and i look forward to it having its own thread

		

